<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p>An embedded-atom method (EAM) potential is employed to describe interactions between all the atoms, and the total energy, 
 <italic>U</italic>
 <sub>tot,</sub> is given by:
 <disp-formula id="FD1-nanomaterials-09-01617">
  <label>(1)</label>
  <math id="mm1">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>U</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mi>tot</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mstyle displaystyle="true">
      <munder>
       <mo>∑</mo>
       <mi>i</mi>
      </munder>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>U</mi>
        <mi>i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mstyle>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where the energy 
 <italic>U
  <sub>i</sub>
 </italic> of an atom 
 <italic>i</italic> is given by:
 <disp-formula id="FD2-nanomaterials-09-01617">
  <label>(2)</label>
  <math id="mm2">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>U</mi>
      <mi>i</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <msub>
      <mi>F</mi>
      <mi>i</mi>
     </msub>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mstyle displaystyle="true">
        <munder>
         <mo>∑</mo>
         <mrow>
          <mi>j</mi>
          <mo>≠</mo>
          <mi>i</mi>
         </mrow>
        </munder>
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mi>ρ</mi>
          <mi>i</mi>
         </msub>
         <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
         <msub>
          <mi>r</mi>
          <mrow>
           <mi>i</mi>
           <mi>j</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        </mrow>
       </mstyle>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo>+</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mn>1</mn>
      <mn>2</mn>
     </mfrac>
     <mstyle displaystyle="true">
      <munder>
       <mo>∑</mo>
       <mrow>
        <mi>j</mi>
        <mo>≠</mo>
        <mi>i</mi>
       </mrow>
      </munder>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>ϕ</mi>
        <mrow>
         <mi>i</mi>
         <mi>j</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>r</mi>
        <mrow>
         <mi>i</mi>
         <mi>j</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mrow>
     </mstyle>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic>F
  <sub>i</sub>
 </italic> is the embedding energy of atom 
 <italic>i</italic>, 
 <italic>ρ
  <sub>i</sub>
 </italic> is the electron density at site 
 <italic>i</italic> induced by all other atoms in the model, and 
 <italic>ϕ
  <sub>ij</sub>
 </italic> is a pair potential interaction between atoms 
 <italic>i</italic> and 
 <italic>j</italic>.
</p>
